OOC: I am going to assume that Nightlight went a good distance away.
At least an hour&#39;s flight time.

At first there is nothing but silence and emptiness that greets
NIGHTLIGHT as she waits for the inevitable to happen. The day is
beginning to pass as the noonday sun has traveled over head and is
begining to sink towards the horizon.

Then in the distance a trail of dust as some sort of large vehicle
approached NIGHTLIGHT. It was one that was easily recognizable to
NIGHTLIGHT as she had seen it hundreds of times before. It was the
contrail of dust and debris that RODIMUS kicked up as he travelled
across the terrain. However now instead of the familiar reds and
yellows of RODIMUS this was the black and greys of DARK RODIMUS as he
aproached in vehicular mode!

He was still some distance away but he was closing fast!

